@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About — HMGHIP</PageTitle>

<div class="stub-page">
    <div class="stub-hero">
        <div class="stub-icon">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor"><path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm1 15h-2v-6h2v6zm0-8h-2V7h2v2z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h1 class="stub-title">About</h1>
        <p class="stub-lead">HMGHIP — How Many Games Have I Played — is a personal gaming diary built to track every game played across the year, one by one, like a journal you actually want to open.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stub-body">
        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">The Idea</h2>
            <p>Letterboxd nailed it for film: a simple diary that turns watching movies into a collection you're proud of. Games deserve the same. HMGHIP lets you mark any game as Want to Play, Playing, or Finished, log your hours and platform, score it out of ten, and write the review while the credits are still rolling.</p>
            <p>Over time it becomes a record of your gaming life — how many games you finished this year, what you thought of them, and which three you'd defend with your life.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">Built With</h2>
            <ul class="stub-list">
                <li>Blazor WebAssembly (.NET 9) — installable as a PWA</li>
                <li>MudBlazor UI components</li>
                <li>Firebase Auth + Firestore for your data</li>
                <li>RAWG Video Games Database API for the catalog</li>
                <li>A love of games and too much free time</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="stub-card">
            <h2 class="stub-section-title">The Creator</h2>
            <p>Built by one person who kept forgetting which games they'd finished, what they thought of them, and whether that one RPG from three winters ago was actually good or just long. Now there's an app for that.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
